author: claude[bot]
message:
Add ELF support for Linux heap allocation counters

- Enable allocation counters on Linux builds with ASSERTIONS_ENABLED
- Use platform-specific section names: .bunheapcnt for ELF, __DATA,BUNHEAPCNT for Mach-O
- Implement ELF parsing using dl_iterate_phdr() to walk sections and symbols
- Fix include structure per review comment by moving mach-o headers inside proper conditional
- Mirror macOS functionality for parsing Bun__allocationCounter__Bun__<Type> symbols

Co-authored-by: Jarred-Sumner <Jarred-Sumner@users.noreply.github.com>

author: JhumanJ
message:
Refactor access token abilities and update policies for granular permissions

- Updated AccessTokenAbility enum to use hyphenated naming for granular scopes (e.g., 'forms-read' instead of 'forms:read').
- Modified FormPolicy, SubmissionPolicy, and WorkspacePolicy to align with new ability names.
- Enhanced WorkspaceController to authorize workspace creation.
- Adjusted ImpersonationMiddleware to use Auth facade for consistency.
- Updated API documentation to reflect changes in ability names and routes.

These changes improve consistency in naming conventions and enhance the authorization checks across the application.

author: JhumanJ
message:
Refactor API documentation structure and remove deprecated OpenAPI JSON file

- Updated the API Reference section in `docs/docs.json` to use a new structure for the OpenAPI source, switching from a JSON file to a YAML file located in the `api-reference` directory.
- Deleted the obsolete `openapi.json` file as part of the transition to the new documentation format.

These changes streamline the API documentation and improve maintainability by adopting a more flexible YAML format.

author: JhumanJ
message:
Implement submission deletion and refactor routes for submissions

- Added a `destroy` method in `FormSubmissionController` to handle the deletion of submissions, allowing for better management of form data.
- Refactored routes in `api/routes/api.php` to group submission-related endpoints under a prefix, improving organization and readability.
- Removed the obsolete `RecordController` and its associated routes, consolidating functionality within the `FormSubmissionController`.
- Updated the `AuthenticateWithJwtOrSanctum` middleware to correct the configuration key for allowed routes, ensuring proper route validation.

These changes enhance the API's functionality by streamlining submission management and improving code organization.

author: JhumanJ
message:
Remove obsolete migration commands and tests

- Deleted the `EmailNotificationMigration` and `FormTitleMigration` command files as they are no longer needed, streamlining the command structure.
- Removed associated test files for the deleted migrations to maintain code cleanliness and avoid confusion.
- Updated the `Kernel.php` to reflect the removal of the middleware and ensure proper middleware management.
- Adjusted the `api/routes/api.php` to maintain route organization after the migration command deletions.

These changes enhance the maintainability of the codebase by removing unused components and ensuring that only relevant code remains.

author: JhumanJ
message:
Refactor access token abilities and update authorization policies

- Removed obsolete `SubmissionPolicy` as its functionality has been integrated into the `FormPolicy`, streamlining the authorization process.
- Updated the `AccessTokenAbility` enum to remove submission-related abilities, focusing on form-related permissions.
- Modified the `FormController` and `ListFormsController` to use the new `ownsWorkspace` authorization method, enhancing clarity and consistency in permission checks.
- Adjusted the `FormPolicy` to include logic for checking write abilities based on the current access token, ensuring proper authorization for form creation.
- Updated API documentation to reflect changes in ability names and routes, improving clarity for developers.

These changes enhance the maintainability and clarity of the authorization system by consolidating policies and refining access control mechanisms.

author: JhumanJ
message:
Add successful response description to OpenAPI documentation

- Added a "200" response description for the Zapier GET endpoint in the OpenAPI YAML file, clarifying the expected successful response for developers.

This change improves the API documentation by providing clear expectations for the response structure, enhancing developer understanding and integration.

Fix X25519 deriveBits to return 32 bytes when length is null

X25519 shared secret (32 bytes), not an empty result. The early return
for !length was preventing the unifiedCallback from properly handling
this case.

author: claude[bot]
message:
Fix duplicate exports by deduplicating in entry point tail generation

Move deduplication logic from computeCrossChunkDependencies to generateEntryPointTailJS where entry points actually generate their export statements. The previous fix only affected non-entry-point chunks but entry points use a different code path through generateEntryPointTailJS.

- Revert changes to computeCrossChunkDependencies.zig that skipped cross-chunk exports for entry points
- Add deduplication logic in generateEntryPointTailJS to remove duplicate export aliases before creating export clause
- Preserves original order and only processes when multiple export items exist

Fixes test failure where duplicate exports were still present in entry point chunks.

🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)

Co-authored-by: Jarred-Sumner <Jarred-Sumner@users.noreply.github.com>

author: claude[bot]
message:
Fix duplicate exports in cross-chunk generation for mixed imports

Add deduplication logic to cross-chunk export generation to prevent
duplicate exports when both static and dynamic imports of CommonJS 
modules are used with code splitting.

The issue was that exports could be generated in two separate paths:
1. Cross-chunk export generation (no deduplication) 
2. Entry point tail generation (had deduplication)

This caused duplicate exports like `export { $bar, $bar }` in scenarios
with mixed static/dynamic imports, leading to syntax errors.

Co-authored-by: Jarred-Sumner <Jarred-Sumner@users.noreply.github.com>

author: claude[bot]
message: `bun run zig-format`

author: Jarred-Sumner
message:
A
    Fix duplicate exports in code splitting by coordinating cross-chunk and entry point export generation

    This commit resolves issue #5344 where duplicate export statements were generated
    when using code splitting with entry points that are imported by other entry points.

    The root cause was that two separate systems were both generating export statements
    for the same symbols:

    1. Cross-chunk export generation (computeCrossChunkDependencies.zig)
    2. Entry point tail generation (postProcessJSChunk.zig)

    When a file serves as both an entry point AND is imported by another entry point,
    both systems would create exports, resulting in syntax errors like:
    `export { a }; export { a };`

    The fix adds coordination between these systems by:
    - Adding deduplication logic in cross-chunk export generation to prevent internal duplicates
    - Filtering out exports in entry point tail generation that are already handled by cross-chunk exports
    - Only generating export statements when there are actual items to export

    This ensures that each symbol is exported exactly once, preventing duplicate export
    syntax errors while maintaining correct code splitting functionality.

    Test cases updated to verify the fix works correctly and doesn't regress.

    🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)

    Co-authored-by: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
